File: Cricket SA's Interim Board and its Members' Council are at loggerheads once again. (eNCA) JOHANNESBURG - Sports Minister Nathi Mthethwa has thrown the ball back into the CSA Members Council's court over the future of the Cricket South Africa board make-up.
Mthethwa has given the Council until 6 April to reconsider its stance. READ: Cricket SA | Governance in the spotlight The Sports Ministry wants the council to agree with the Interim Board and ensure the recommendations of the 2013 Nicholson inquiry are implemented, specifically those concerning the number of independent directors on the new Board of Directors. The Interim Board and the Members' Council have been at loggerheads these last few weeks over the implementation of Nicholson's recommendations.